&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pain Management Clinical Nurse Specialist - Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has risen for an enthusiastic, dynamic and committed individual to join the Pain Service Team at Kingston Hospital Foundation Trust (KHFT). We are looking for someone who is motivated, energetic, and hardworking, with experience and knowledge of pain assessment, management and evaluation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You must be an RGN with 3 years (minimum) post registration experience within the acute setting and educated to a Master level or with equivalent experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Pain service team at KHFT cover both a busy acute inpatient service and a productive chronic outpatient service. They are small, friendly proactive and dynamic team; ensuring outstanding care is provided to the patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: Week commencing 30th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sarah Shade on:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;020 8946 7711 Ext 2914 / &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;s.shade@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; or Margaret Uchendu at: m.uchendu@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
